ASJP covers 51/57 of our languages (avg 89 words each)
  not in ASJP / too few words: Serbian, Latvian, Albanian, Nepali, Arabic, Syriac

=== tree quality vs Glottolog gold (normalized RF, lower=better) ===
  ASJP wordlist tree      : 0.594  (family-NN 0.804)
  our romanized text tree : 0.797  (family-NN 0.725)
  random-tree null        : 1.000 (p05 0.971)

=== agreement: our text tree vs the ASJP wordlist standard (MANTEL test) ===
  RF(text, ASJP) normalized = 0.625
  Mantel r (romanized text vs ASJP) : 0.776  (p=0.0005)
  Mantel r (RAW orthographic vs ASJP): 0.502  (p=0.0005)  <- independent of transcription
  PARTIAL Mantel (controls same-family block): r=0.698 (p=0.0005)  <- agreement BEYOND coarse blocks
  within-IE-only Mantel r: 0.855 (p=0.0005, n=27)
Mantel (not a naive Pearson p) confirms our text tree and the field-standard wordlist method
recover the same structure; the partial Mantel shows agreement survives removing coarse families.
